      • readFromFile

        public static ChemblConfig readFromFile()
                                 throws IOException
        Reads the configuration for the ChEMBL proxy from a properties file chembl-adapter.properties in the classpath. The properties' keys are:
        • ep.chembl.adapter.bioactivities.assays.min: (integer) minimum number of assays required to filter a bioactivity.
        • ep.chembl.adapter.bioactivities.assays.functional.min: (double) minimum fraction of functional assays ("data measuring the biological effect of a compound") required to filter a bioactivity.
        • ep.chembl.adapter.bioactivities.assays.confidence4.min: (double) minimum fraction of assays with a confidence 4 ("Multiple homologous protein targets may be assigned") or higher required to filter a bioactivity.
        • ep.chembl.adapter.bioactivities.assays.confidence9.min: (double) minimum fraction of assays with a confidence 9 ("Direct single protein target assigned") or higher required to filter a bioactivity.
        • ep.chembl.adapter.ws.url.base: the base URL for ChEMBL web services.
        For confidence levels, see also the table CONFIDENCE_SCORE_LOOKUP in ChEMBL schema.
        Returns:
        A configuration object with its fields set to the values from the properties file (or the default values, if missing there).
        Throws:
        IOException - in case of trouble loading the properties.
